# Commit Required For Substantive Changes

When the task includes substantive changes, the agent must output a git commit in the same turn.

## When this rule is triggered

- Feature addition, feature behavior change, or bug fix.
- Any implementation that changes runtime behavior (not only analysis/explanation).

## Required actions

1. Stage only relevant files.
2. Create a commit with a clear message explaining why the change is made.
3. Report commit hash and changed files in the final response.

## Exception

- If there is no code/config/content change to commit, explicitly state that no commit was created.
